<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3564] Memory leak in Filterindex / ServiceRegistryCache</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3564</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The filter indexes in the ServiceRegistryCache caches ServiceListeners for a faster lookup.&lt;br/&gt;
However, once a ServiceListener is stored in the cache, it will never be released which will eventually lead to an OutOfMemoryError.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is caused by the implementation of BundleContextIntercepter#removeServiceListener.&lt;br/&gt;
While debugging, it appears the cache has no filterindex for arguments null,null and thus leaving the listener in the cache.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Linux Mint 12, x64, Dell E6520</environment>
        <key id="12595058">FELIX-3564</key>
