                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13396834" author="uiterlix" created="Tue, 19 Jun 2012 14:51:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by a rather brute force call to FilterIndex.removeListener() for two reasons:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It aligns nicely with the BundleContext.removeListener() API which promises to do nothing when a listener is passed that is not available in this bundleContext;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Another solution would be to explicitly keep track in the ServiceRegistryCache of what listener is registered with which FilterIndex,  It&apos;s cheaper in memory consumption to have the indices perform an unnecessary map.remove(). The extra processing overhead is negligible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13396836" author="uiterlix" created="Tue, 19 Jun 2012 14:52:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See comment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
